142A 101st Legislative Session 142
2026 South Dakota Legislature
Senate Bill 142
AMENDME NT 142A
FOR THE INTRODUCED BILL
Introduced by: Senator Voita
1 An Act to amend the requirements for filing certain campaign finance disclosure
2 statements.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
4 Section 1. That § 12-27-22 be AMENDED:
5 12-27-22. The treasurer of a political committee listed below shall file a campaign
6 finance disclosure statement or a report the following campaign finance disclosure
7 statements with the secretary of state as follows:
8 (1) For a candidate or candidate campaign committee for any statewide office, file a
9 pre-primary, pre-general, year-end, and, if applicable, supplemental report and
10 amendments in even numbered years and in odd numbered years, file a year-end
11 report and, if applicable, amendments:
12 (a) A pre-primary statement;
13 (b) A pre-general statement;
14 (c) A An annual year-end statement;
15 (d) A supplemental report as provided in § 12-27-28, if applicable; and
16 (e) In even-numbered years, if If applicable, amendments to any information
17 provided on a prior statement;
18 (2) For a candidate or candidate campaign committee for a legislative or county office
19 with a recognized political party, file a pre-primary, a pre-general, year-end and,
20 if applicable, supplemental report and amendments in even numbered years:
21 (a) A pre-primary statement;
22 (b) A pre-general statement;
23 (c) A An annual year-end statement, annually;
24 (d) A supplemental report as provided in § 12-27-28, if applicable; and
25 (e) In even-numbered years, if If applicable, amendments to any information
26 provided on a prior statement;
