142A 3 142
1 (e) In even-numbered years, if If applicable, amendments to any information
2 provided on a prior statement.
3 The treasurer of a political committee listed in this section may submit a
4 termination report statement at any time.
5 If a political party loses the status of a qualified party, the party must file a
6 termination report statement by five p.m. central time on the last Friday in January
7 following the calendar year in which the qualified party status was lost. If a statewide
8 ballot question committee does not list any activity on the next required campaign finance
9 report statement submitted to the secretary of state, that committee has until the next
10 reporting period to report activity. If that committee does not have any activity to report
11 by the next reporting period, the committee must submit a termination report statement
12 by that reporting period deadline.
13 A violation of this section is a Class 2 misdemeanor. A subsequent offense within
14 a calendar year is a Class 1 misdemeanor.
15 Section 2. This Act is effective beginning January 1, 2027.
